 {"id":"frankenjax-go1z","title":"Cumsum/Cumprod panic on empty tensors","description":"[HIGH] eval_cumulative in crates/fj-lax/src/reduction.rs computes outer_count = total / axis_dim after axis_dim = tensor.shape.dims[axis] as usize. For a valid empty tensor on the selected axis, e.g. TensorValue::new(DType::I64, Shape { dims: vec![0] }, vec![]), axis_dim == 0 and total == 0, so Primitive::Cumsum/Primitive::Cumprod panic with division by zero. Repro: call eval_primitive(Primitive::Cumsum, &[input], &BTreeMap::new()); the same applies to Cumprod and axis=-1. Expected JAX/NumPy behavior is to return an empty tensor with the same shape/dtype. Add regression tests for shape [0] and a zero-sized selected axis such as [2,0] axis 1, then return early when axis_dim == 0.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T06:15:10.037676065Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-30T17:30:53.431236181Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T17:30:53.429367952Z","close_reason":"Added public eval_primitive empty-axis cumsum/cumprod regression coverage; existing implementation returns empty tensors without panic.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
